<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1>
	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		<td valign=middle align=right class="header">Creating A Form</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Insert the <em>Form Name, Header </em>and <em>Submission Message</em>.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">
			Select a form user Type: <br>
			<li><em>Public</em>: All users are able to access the form.</li>
			<li><em>Private</em>: Only selected user(s) is(are) able to access the form.</li>
			<li><em>Group</em>: Only selected group(s) is(are) able to access the form.</li>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Select <strong>Yes</strong> for<em> Save To Database</em> option. This indicates the data submitted will be saved into database.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">4.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Insert e-mail address(es) of the form administrator in the <em>Email To field</em>.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">5.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Select user by clicking on the <strong>Select</strong> button for the <em>Message via Intranet To</em>. This will send notification to the selected user via Intranet message.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">6.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Select user(s) in <em>Allow Query By</em> column will allow the selected user to query the saved data (provided that user has selected <strong>Yes</strong> in Step 3).</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">7.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Selecting <strong>Yes</strong> in<em> Approval Required</em> option will indicate the form submission requires approval from the selected user(s).</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">8.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">To link to another form, select a form using the pulldown menu. This indicates the user will be directed to the selected form upon submission.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">9.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Using the <strong>Copy Field</strong> function, user can copy all the form fields from the selected form and insert it into the current form. <br> 10. Insert a number into the <em>Table Column</em> field to format the form. Default is 2.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">10.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Save</strong> button to move on to create fields in the form.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
